The paper deals with the complexity of polytopes and their projections, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of semidefinite programming and factorizations suggests a connection to optimization and algorithms (cs.DS, cs.CC). The rescaling technique used in the proof may also have information-theoretic implications (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents a lower bound on the extension complexity of a specific type of polytope, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
